<div id="rules-container-2" class="row rules-container">
    <div class="text-center col-xs-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
        <h1 class="game-title">Smash 4</h1>
        <article class="text-collapsible secondary-font text-left">
            <span class="rules-heading">Match Layout</span>
            <p>Each game will last 6 minutes with each player starting with 2 stock. Matches will be won when one player wins 2 matches (Best of 3).</p>
            
            <span class="rules-heading">Tournament Structure</span>
            <p>The tournament will be a double elimination tournament with no items, no custom characters/moves, no handicaps, damage ratio set to 1x, and pausing will be disabled.</p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Stages</span>
            <p>First stage will be decided via rock paper scissors, witht he loser choosing the next stage. Stage much be agreed upon by contestants every time.</p>
            <p>Stages allowed: <ul>
                <li>Battlefield</li>
                <li>Dream Land 64</li>
                                   <li>Final Destination</li>
                                   <li>Smashville</li>
                                   <li>Town &amp; City</li>
                <li>Lylat Cruise</li>
                <li>&Omega; Midgar</li>
                <li>&Omega; Suzaku Castle</li>
                <li>&Omega; Wily Castle</li>
                </ul></p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Character Selection</span>
            <p>Amiibo will be banned. Mii Fighters are allowed as default guest characters.</p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Controllers</span>
            <p>Controllers must be disconnected before and after matches.</p>
            <p>Permitted Controllers: <ul>
                <li>Gamecube</li>
                <li>Wii U Pro</li>
                <li>Wii U Gamepad</li>
                <li>Wii Remote Variations</li>
                </ul></p>
        </article>
        <a id="read-more-2" class="read-more-link" href="javascript:void(0)" data-bind="click: function() { toggleShow('read-more-2') }">Read More</a>
    </div>
