<div id="rules-container-3" class="row rules-container">
    <div class="text-center col-xs-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
        <h1 class="game-title">League of Legends</h1>
        <article class="text-collapsible secondary-font text-left">
            <span class="rules-heading">Registration</span>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Players must have ownership of the account(s) registered.</li>
                    <li>Up to two subsitute players may be registered on the roster. They may NOT be registered as part of any other team.</li>
                    <li>Up to one (1) Team Manager may be provided on the team registration. The team manager cannot be used as an additional substitute slot.</li>
                    <li>
                        Rosters:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Participants must register as a premade team of 5-7.</li>
                            <li>Team Captains of Team managers are responsible for registration and providing accurate information of all the players on the roster.</li>
                            <li>Rosters are locked and cannot be changed after the team plays its first game.</li>
                            <li>Any player who is not listed on a team's roster is considered ineligible to play.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>Players must be able to attend the LAN event in order to be eligible</li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Tournament Structure</span>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        The tournament will have one stage:
                        <ol>
                            <li>The LAN will be held starting on September 30, at 10AM in the Ohio Union's Great Hall at The Ohio State University.</li>
                            <li>The tournament will be a Best of 1 throughout the entirety of the tournament, with the semi-finals being Best of 3, and finals being Best of 5. *Note: Finals may be changed to Best of 3 depending on time.</li>
                            <li>Finals will start 15 minutes after the end of the last semi-final game.</li>
                            <li>Matches will be allotted 1 hour to be played. Therefore, rounds will begin ever 1 hour, with the exception of a break for dinner.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Scheduling Rules</span>
            <p>
                LAN and Finals
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        General Schedule
                        <ol>
                            <li>Players will be afforded at least ten minutes between matches.</li>
                            <li>If a team is still missing a player 10 minutes after the allotted 10 minute break, the team will lose a ban, and will continue to lose one ban every 5 minutes up to 3 bans, after which, the team will be disqualified.</li>
                            <li>The tournament will begin at 11:00AM Eastern Time. Check-in will begin at 10:00AM and end at 10:45AM.</li>
                            <li>If a position in the bracket is empty because the winning team was disqualified, it will be filled by the losing team of that game.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Match Rules</span>
            <p>
                Game Format: All games must be played using hte Tournament Draft Mode through a custom game lobby on the PVP.net client.
                <ol>
                    <li>Only 5 players are allowed to enter the match for each team. Spectators (other than administrators or coaches) are not allowed for the online match.</li>
                    <li>Teams using an illegal substitute or ineligible player as described above will be disqualified.</li>
                    <li>Lobby Host can start the game when both teams have indicated they are ready in lobby chat.</li>
                    <li>Any team missing players may elect to play with fewer than five players, forfeit the game, or forfeit the entire match. If the team elects to forfeit a single game, they will have an additional 15 minutes for the missing player to arrive.</li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Gameplay</span>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        Pauses:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Each team is allowed fifteen minutes of pause time.</li>
                            <li>Disruptions include: unintentional disconnection, server instability, computer or peripheral malfunction, or other unavoidable interruption.</li>
                            <li>The opposing team may allow for pauses longer than fifteen minutes.</li>
                            <li>Both teams must confirm readiness before pause resume.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Chat Function:
                        <ol>
                            <li>All chat should be used minimally to talk with the other team. Communications should be limited to sportsmanline conduct, communication regarding pauses, and rule clarifications.</li>
                            <li>Unsportsmanlike conduct will not be tolerated and will result in a disqualification.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Restrictions:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Any champion that is released after or 1 week prior to the tournament will be unavailable for use throughout the tournament.</li>
                            <li>If a crash occurs during picks and bans, teams may decide whether to re-pick entirely or maintain the same picks up until the point of the crash.</li>
                            <li>If a glitch in the client occurs and runes, summoner spells, and/or masteries of a player did not get locked, then your team is allowed one restart per set and must be done before the 1 minute mark of the game.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Side Picks: 
                        <ol>
                            <li>Best of 1: The team on the top of the bracket ("Home Team") has choice of side.</li>
                            <li>Best of 3: The Home Team has choice of side for games 1 and 3, while Away Team has choice for game 2.</li>
                            <li>Best of 5: Home Team has has choice of side for games 1 and 3, while Away Team has choice for game 2 and 4. Game 5 will be decided by a coin toss performed by an administrator.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Fatal Errors:
                        <ol>
                            <li>A game may be restarted if disruptions occur before first blood or 3 minutes into the game.</li>
                            <li>In the case of game crashes, the team will recreate the games with the same bans and picks.
                            <ol>
                                <li>If the crash is a result of an item bug, the player must change their loadout.</li>
                                <li>If the crash is confirmed to be a result of a specific champion, the teams will recreate the game with new picks and bans.</li>
                                </ol></li>
                            <li>If a match cannot be played out due to server instability, the match will be rescheduled to another date.</li>
                            <li>Any stoppage of play resulting in server instability must be confirmed by third party sources, such as time-stamped Riot or forum posts.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Disruptive Play:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Unfair play or misbehavior will result in immediate suspension of th eoffending player(s) from the tournament and their team(s) may face disqualification at the discretion of administrators depending on the number and severity of infractions. This includes, but is not limited to, the following list:
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Unsportsmanlike conduct. This includes, but is not limited to:
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Either team excessively calling premature 'gg'</li>
                                        <li>Offensive language</li>
                                        <li>Inappropriate use of /all chat function</li>
                                        <li>General 'Bad Manners'</li>
                                        <li>Abuse of the pause function (aka Puppey Pause)</li>
                                        <li>Intentional disconnection without prior communication</li>
                                        <li>Colluding with another player or team</li>
                                        <li>Use of cheats</li>
                                        </ol></li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <span class="rules-heading">Administrative Decisions</span>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        Email:
                        <ol>
                            <li>Emails sent through the administrator can make any executive decision not covered in the rules.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        LAN and Finals
                        <ol>
                            <li>Any decisions made by administrators are final.</li>
                            <li>Any issues that are not covered above in the rules are left to the discretion of the administrators.</li>
                            <li>If an individual believes that an administrator has made an error, either by mistake or malice, they are to make a first attempt to resolve it privately with that administrator. If no resolution can be found, please message Yugen directly at <a href="mailto:ben@yugen.gg">ben@yugen.gg</a> to request an internal investigation.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </article>
        <a id="read-more-3" class="read-more-link" href="javascript:void(0)" data-bind="click: function() { toggleShow('read-more-3') }">Read More</a>
    </div>
</div>

